# RPT report signed colors (text)

When a **report overlay** under `WpfUserControlFramework/Controls/RPT Dashboard/` uses **green or red for text** (e.g. positive/negative growth, signed variance, value above/below zero), use the shared theme brushes only — do not invent new hex values in local `UserControl.Resources` or code-behind.

| Role | Hex | Theme key |
|------|-----|-----------|
| Positive / favorable | `#22C55E` | `Brush.RptReportPositiveForeground` |
| Negative / unfavorable | `#DC2626` | `Brush.RptReportNegativeForeground` |

Defined in `WpfUserControlFramework/PeoplePosTheme.xaml` next to other `Brush.Rpt*` resources.

## XAML

- Bind `Foreground` (or `Stroke` on trend icons that pair with that text) with `{StaticResource Brush.RptReportPositiveForeground}` / `{StaticResource Brush.RptReportNegativeForeground}`.

## Code-behind

- Prefer `Application.Current.TryFindResource("Brush.RptReportPositiveForeground")` (and negative) with a **frozen fallback** `SolidColorBrush` using the same hex values if the app dictionary is not merged yet (see `RptDeliveryVarianceReportOverlay` / `RptTillDrawerVarianceReportOverlay`).

## Out of scope

- Non-report UI (Staff, Procurement, Operations) may keep its own palette; this rule targets **RPT Dashboard report overlays** only unless a task explicitly extends it.
